question: Format answer for: Regarding patient 'AII-11' from family 'Family A': What is the pathogenicity classification for the third mutation?
context:
Information not found.

The document states: "Patients carrying the p.D620N mutation did not have any other variants in all exons of VPS35." (Page 3, first paragraph under "Results"). Patient AII-11 from Family A is one of the patients identified with the p.D620N mutation (Figure 1A, Table 1, Table 2). Therefore, according to this document, patient AII-11 was found to have only one mutation (p.D620N) in the VPS35 gene. There is no mention of a second or third mutation for this patient within the VPS35 gene, nor is there information provided about mutations in other genes specifically for patient AII-11.
